        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 6:05PM CST by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 605 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Gustine, or 14 miles west of Hamilton, moving east at
50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Hamilton
and southeastern Comanche Counties, including the following
locations... Lamkin, Energy, Pottsville, Olin, Gentrys Mill, Carlton,
and Indian Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
